<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-06-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-06-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 296/379: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kellogg</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-06-24T20:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">June 24,
                                        1924—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 24—7:05
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>223. Have just received invitation referred to in my 220, June 18, 4 p.m.
                            It is in form of long memorandum setting forth views of British
                            Government and urging American participation. It is now being coded, and
                            will be sent tomorrow morning at latest.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>